This paper is about neural machine translation (NMT) and its impact on post-editing productivity in the banking and finance domain. Therefore, it is most likely to belong to the category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper uses empirical testing and machine learning techniques, which suggest that it could also belong to the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with information retrieval and domain-specific data, which could place it in the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of NMT in a specific domain, which could make it relevant to the category of Cybersecurity (cs.CY).
